## Why This Is Asked

This question tests practical integration of workload identity with policy enforcement in a CNF gateway, emphasizing data governance, per-tenant isolation, and non-disruptive upgrades. It requires concrete steps for credential rotation, policy encoding, runtime checks, and observability.

## Key Concepts

- SPIRE SVIDs and workload attestation for multitenant isolation
- OPA Gatekeeper policy modeling per tenant (retention windows, redaction rules)
- Runtime log redaction and per-tenant observability
- Kind-based local testbed for end-to-end verification
- Zero-downtime rollout with traffic shaping and drift checks

## Code Example

```javascript
function redactLog(entry, policy) {
  const redacted = { ...entry };
  (policy.redactFields || []).forEach(field => {
    if (redacted.hasOwnProperty(field)) redacted[field] = "***REDACTED***";
  });
  return redacted;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you rotate SVIDs across tenants with revocation semantics in SPIRE?
- How would you validate redaction coverage across logs in CI/CD and production?

## Why This Is Asked
This question probes multi-tenant CNF provenance at scale, including per-tenant keys, drift detection, rollback, and observability.

## Key Concepts
- Tenant-scoped key management
- Per-tenant SBOMs and provenance enforcement
- ImagePolicyWebhook + OPA constraints
- Drift detection and tenant-aware rollback
- Observability: metrics, traces, audit logs

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudo-code: verify image provenance per tenant
async function verifyProvenance(imageRef, tenant) {
  const sigOk = await cosign.verify(imageRef, { key: `kms://${tenant}-key` });
  const sbom = await fetchSBOM(imageRef);
  if (sbom.tenant !== tenant) throw new Error('Tenant SBOM mismatch');
  return sigOk;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you rotate tenant keys without downtime?
- How would you test drift detection across regions?

## Why This Is Asked
This question tests the ability to design a comprehensive cross-architecture supply chain security and runtime trust workflow that addresses edge deployment challenges, including offline scenarios and real-time policy enforcement.

## Key Concepts
- Per-architecture image signing and SBOM provenance tracking
- Runtime attestation with architecture-aware claim verification
- Policy enforcement using OPA Gatekeeper with architecture-specific constraints
- Edge connectivity management and canary-driven rollback mechanisms

## Code Example
```javascript
function isAllowed(image, arch) {
  // Verify Cosign signature for specific architecture
  const signatureValid = verifyCosignSignature(image, arch);
  const sbomPresent = checkSBOMPresence(image, arch);
  const attestationValid = verifyInTotoAttestation(image, arch);

  return signatureValid && sbomPresent && attestationValid;
}
```

